<p>I am trying to download a dist/codeLib.js from myPrivateGitRepo to anotherGitRepo</p>  <p>In bower.json of anotherGitRepo, I kept</p>  <pre><code>"dependencies":{     "myPrivateGitRepo":"git://github.company.com/username/myPrivateGitRepo.git#0.0.1"   }, </code></pre>  <p>by following <a href="https://docs.npmjs.com/files/package.json#git-urls-as-dependencies" rel="nofollow">https://docs.npmjs.com/files/package.json#git-urls-as-dependencies</a> this is working and downloading entire project inside node_modules of anotherGitRepo.</p>  <p>but I just want to create a gitURL , so that it only download dist/codeLib.js OF myPrivateGitRepo into anotherGitRepo</p>  <p>may be something like</p>  <pre><code>"dependencies":{     "myPrivateGitRepo":"git://github.company.com/username/myPrivateGitRepo.git#0.0.1-forCodeLibJS"   } </code></pre>  <p>how to do that?</p>  <p><strong>update :</strong>  I added </p>  <pre><code>"ignore": [     "folder1",     "folder2"     //Except dist   ] </code></pre>  <p>to the myPrivateGitRepo bower.json.</p>  <p>cd into anotherGitRepo in local and did bower install, but bower_components is downloading everything from git and surprisingly dist/* is not.</p>  <blockquote>   <p>worked :</p> </blockquote>  <p>I added the ignore list in the bower.json of myPrivateGitRepo and in bower.json of  anotherGitRepo , I added the gitURL for eg. <code>git://github.company.com/username/myPrivateGitRepo.git#privateTag</code> </p>  <p>cd into anotherGitRepo and did bower install. It imported all the files from <em>myPrivateGitRepo</em> except the ignored list.</p>